me.choco.locksecurity.api

Class LockedBlock

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.choco.locksecurity.api.LockedBlock
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JSONSerializable

    public class LockedBlock
extends java.lang.Object
implements JSONSerializable
    Represents a block in which contains information about its owner, Lock ID, Key ID and position in the world. This may take various forms as different types of blocks may be locked
    Author:
    Parker Hawke - 2008Choco

      • setSecondaryComponent

        public void setSecondaryComponent(LockedBlock secondaryComponent)
        Set the secondary component of this block. The secondary component MUST be of the same type and must be a valid contendor, such as DoubleChest or Door components. This locked block and the specified component will be linked together
        Parameters:
        secondaryComponent - the block to set as a secondary component
        Throws:
        IllegalBlockPositionException - if the block is not positioned correctly

      • setSecondaryComponent

        public void setSecondaryComponent(LockedBlock secondaryComponent,
                                  boolean force)
        Set the secondary component of this block. The secondary component MUST be of the same type and must be a valid contendor, such as DoubleChest or Door components. This locked block and the specified component will be linked together.
        If forced, the components will be linked regardless of their block position / state
        Parameters:
        secondaryComponent - the block to set as a secondary component
        force - if true, the blocks will be linked together regardless of their position
        Throws:
        IllegalBlockPositionException - if the block is not positioned correctly (and "force" is false)
